    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-04T00:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-04T00:54:00-05:00" n="718"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.79690F/9–444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister to Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-04T09:00:00+03:06"
                            >September 4, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>265. Received reply from Saudi Arabian Government to Legation note July 29
                    requesting on behalf of Commanding General <pb facs="0675" n="663"
                        xml:id="pg_663"/> USAFIME<note n="11" xml:id="d718fn11">Maj. Gen. Benjamin
                        F. Giles, Commanding General, U.S. Army Forces in the Middle East
                        (USAFIME).</note> permission to make aerial and engineering surveys for
                    direct air route Cairo to Dhahran.</p>
                <p>Summary as follows: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Proposed air route raises serious problems. Studies and discussions to
                            remove great obstacles must precede decision to grant permission or
                            not.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Before decision can be made to permit surveys or not Saudi Arabian
                            Government must know detailed survey program: Exactly when the surveys
                            would take place; whether planes will land; whence they come, which
                            direction they go, whether each returns each time to point of takeoff.
                            Furthermore, route should be shifted further to north, if, as appears on
                            map furnished, it would pass close to Jauf, Tayma and Hayil. End
                            summary.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Complete text<note n="12" xml:id="d718fn12">Text not printed; in his covering
                        despatch 1, September 4, the Minister in Saudi Arabia said: “It would appear
                        that careful and detailed negotiations with the Saudi Arabian Government
                        will be necessary before progress can be expected in this important matter.”
                        (883.79690F/9–444)</note> follows by air pouch.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Cairo for Giles.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
